{
  "stem": "1581.3",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And again, you know, optimism, you say, well, if you work very hard, the life is better there.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So they foolishly believed it.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I mean, sooner or later they would have been transported anyway, but they volunteered.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And I only have one sign of life from my sister, which I recovered after the war.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "That was one plain postcard which was a standard saying that she was well and she needs packages of food.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And it was mailed from a little Polish town called [NON-ENGLISH], and I have no idea where she disappeared and how.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "There was no trace about her husband whatsoever.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "That's all I know about the fate of my only sister.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So we were in Theresienstadt, my mother, my wife, our adorable little baby, and I.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And as the time went by, we somehow got, again, adjusted to the new situation.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Can you describe, like, a typical day in Theresienstadt?",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, I worked as a physician, and the first few weeks, as I said, my wife was in the hospital and sick.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "My baby was in a children's home and, I must say, very well taken care of.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And my mother had odd jobs that the ghetto could offer.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "She helped out as much as she could, and of course she was an enormous help with the baby, also.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We lived-- the men lived in barracks called the Sudeten barracks.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "They were-- since it was a military garrison, there were a lot of military barracks there.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "There was the Dresden barracks, which was for females.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "There was a Hamburger barracks where all young women were located.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "There was a Kavalir barracks, which was transformed into an old-age and a hospital for hopeless diseases.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "There was another one reserved for mentally disturbed, and there was the famous [?",
      "word_count": 14
    }
  ],
